en_604467_0	Minister Ranjith Maddumabandara says the cabinet approval has been granted to provide land deeds to all the people who have settled in government owned lands.
en_604467_1	Ranjith Maddumabandara was speaking at the Cabinet media briefing that was held at the Government Information Department today.
en_604467_2	He noted that former Prime Minister D S Senanayake was the first leader who ensured land rights of the people by passing a new law.
en_604467_3	Former Minister Gamini Dissanayake also took measures to provide Swarna-bhoomi land deeds to the people in rural areas.
en_604467_4	The current government has taken a decision to give land deeds to the people who have settled in state lands in the near future.
en_604467_5	The Minister further said that the Southern Expressway was extended to Matara under the present government.
en_604467_6	He pointed out that, by September, the Southern Expressway that was extended to Mattala, will be vested with the people.
